parts.text:
commit till now changes of each file and now Let's bring in the Pinhole Camera. This is often the most "magical" moment for a Class 6 student because it proves a fundamental rule of the universe: Light travels in straight lines. When they see that the image of a candle is flipped upside down simply because of a tiny hole, the concept of "Rectilinear Propagation of Light" clicks instantly.

1. Updating the UI (index.html)
We’ll add the third experiment card to your sidebar. Notice how we are building a "Gallery" of experiments.

HTML
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mt-6">
    <h3 class="font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
        <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-indigo-500 rounded-full mr-2"></span>
        Experiment 3: Pinhole Camera
    </h3>
    <p class="text-sm mb-4 opacity-70">Move the candle to see how the image flips inside the camera.</p>

    <button onclick="setMode('pinhole')" class="interactive-btn w-full p-3 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium active-tab">
        Launch Camera Lab
    </button>
</div>
2. The Pinhole Logic (script.js)
We will add a function that draws the "Camera" (the box), the candle, and most importantly, the inverted image.

JavaScript
